 ## [Unreleased]
 
+### Added — self-contained macOS and Linux release artifacts
+
+- Added digest-pinned Tebako/Ruby builders for macOS arm64 and glibc Linux x86_64, deterministic archives with runtime assets, and Ruby-free CLI/daemon/TUI/native-gem smoke gates.
+- Added a strict canonical `release.json`/`SHA256SUMS` finalizer plus keyless checksum signing and GitHub build-provenance attestations. Signed semver tags must equal `Hive::VERSION`; release automation never moves an existing tag.
+- Added XDG global paths, copy-only legacy migration, and a versioned `.hive/project.yml` pointer while retaining `.hive-state/` as durable project history.
+- Added non-secret provider/model selectors, a full installation doctor, and consent-safe launchd/systemd-user service reconciliation.
+- Added receipt-driven Homebrew, AUR `hive-bin`, and checksum-safe bash channels with collision-safe `hv`, manager-delegated update, and work-preserving uninstall.
+- Added one separately installed Hive operator skill for Claude, Codex, and Pi, plus the host-neutral approval-gated install prompt.
+- Added tier-1 post-publication acceptance gates for Ubuntu bash, macOS Homebrew/launchd, and real Arch AUR/systemd-user environments; a release is not complete until every channel passes.
+- Updated locked `concurrent-ruby`, Faraday, and JSON dependencies to advisory-cleared versions used by the embedded runtime.
+
 ### Added — opt-in interactive tmux brainstorm runtime
 
 - `brainstorm.runtime: tmux_interactive` runs stage `2-brainstorm` in a fresh per-task tmux session (`hive-2-brainstorm-<slug>`) with interactive `claude`, while preserving the existing `brainstorm.md` WAITING/COMPLETE marker contract.
