+---
+name: hive
+description: Install, diagnose, initialize, operate, update, or uninstall the Hive multi-agent workflow safely. Use for Hive setup, `hive doctor`, project/task status and stage transitions, daemon service control, command collisions requiring `hv`, lifecycle channel delegation, and work-preserving cleanup.
+---
+
+# Hive operator
+
+Treat GitHub `ivankuznetsov/hive` releases as the only core source. Never use a
+RubyGem, system Ruby, Bundler, a source clone, or copied skill files as an
+installation fallback.
+
+## Establish the command
+
+1. Try `hive --version`; if it is not an exact semver Hive response, try
+   `hv --version`.
+2. Preserve an unrelated `hive` command. Use the working Hive command for the
+   rest of the session.
+3. Run `<cmd> doctor --json`. Report error, warning, and advisory rows without
+   printing environment secrets.
+
+## Install or repair
+
+- Detect OS, architecture, and native manager read-only.
+- Prefer `brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive` on macOS arm64, `hive-bin`
+  through yay/paru on Arch, and the verified release installer on Ubuntu/Linux.
+- Ask before core installation, marketplace changes, dependency installation,
+  project init/enrollment, or daemon registration/start.
+- Configure only the agent host running this skill. If the host is ambiguous,
+  ask which host; never mutate every detected host.
+- Install llm-wiki, Compound Engineering, and PR Review Toolkit separately
+  through the active host's native package mechanism. Do not vendor them.
+- Never request, accept, or persist API keys. Authentication belongs to the
+  agent CLI, environment, or OS credential store.
+- Require a green `<cmd> doctor --json` error count before offering init.
+
+## Initialize and operate
+
+Before init, show the target main checkout and planned effects. Run
+`<cmd> init <path>` only after approval. Keep `.hive-state/` intact; the
+`.hive/project.yml` file is only its versioned pointer.
+
+Use structured commands for automation:
+
+- `<cmd> status --json`
+- `<cmd> new PROJECT TEXT`
+- `<cmd> brainstorm|plan|develop|open-pr|review|finalize|archive TARGET --json`
+- `<cmd> daemon service install|status|remove`
+- `<cmd> update --dry-run --json` before `<cmd> update`
+- `<cmd> uninstall --dry-run --json` before approved cleanup
+
+Never delete `.hive-state/` or XDG workflow state. Core uninstall does not
+remove this agent package, other marketplaces, or agent credentials.
